Example of a Pun
The Pun: &ldquo;An ambassador is an honest man sent to lie abroad for the good of his country.&rdquo;
The Play on Words: The word &ldquo;lie&rdquo; has two meanings here: to physically reside in another country and to tell an untruth for diplomatic purposes.
My Own Sentence Using a Pun
&ldquo;I told my doctor that I broke my arm in two places. He told me to stop going to those places.&rdquo;
The Play on Words: The word &ldquo;places&rdquo; switches between locations on the human body and physical geographic locations.
